h4.Summary: 

When a soft hyphen {noformat}&shy;{noformat} is added to a word with formatting (for example ++ __ or **) it will disappear and formatting will work, but if you then copy this word and try to add formatting to the copied word, the formatting will fail.

Please see video for example.

h4.Steps to Reproduce:

* Open a comment on this issue.

* Add the text {noformat} +bug&shy;gy+ {noformat} manually (do not copy this one).

* Preview the comment.

* Copy the preview word *buggy*.

* Try to paste it and put formatting around it.
* Preview the comment.




h4.Expected Results:

The word buggy should be underlined.



h4.Actual Results:

The word shows up as {noformat} +buggy+ {noformat}


h4. Notes

Characters which cause this behavior:
{noformat}
&shy;
&zwnj; 	
&zwj; 	
&lrm; 	
&rlm; 	
{noformat}

